# Component Workflow

## Project Context

| Item          | Value                                                                                              |
| ------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Figma file    | [Idenflu Design System](https://www.figma.com/design/aMK1ysrAI4RGk1mrFk0O41/Idenflu-Design-System) |
| Figma fileKey | `aMK1ysrAI4RGk1mrFk0O41`                                                                           |
| Tokens        | `packages/ui-react/src/styles/tokens.css` → `@idenflu/ui-foundations`                              |
| Package       | `packages/ui-react`                                                                                |

## Source Roles

| Source                               | Use for                                                 |
| ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| Figma MCP                            | Visual specs, variants, spacing, color, typography      |
| MUI MCP (`useMuiDocs` → `fetchDocs`) | Props API, composition                                  |
| Carbon React                         | API and a11y patterns                                   |
| Codebase                             | Final implementation patterns (override generated code) |

Carbon references (until MCP):

- Docs: `https://react.carbondesignsystem.com/`
- Source: `https://github.com/carbon-design-system/carbon/tree/main/packages/react/src/components`

## Figma → Code

When a Figma URL or node is provided:

1. `get_design_context` with fileKey `aMK1ysrAI4RGk1mrFk0O41` and nodeId from URL
2. If Code Connect mapping exists, prefer mapped codebase component
3. Map Figma variables to `@idenflu/ui-foundations` CSS custom properties
4. Adapt reference code to project conventions — do not paste Tailwind or raw hex values
5. Match existing component folder structure (see below)

## API Design (no implementation)

When asked to design props only:

1. Figma MCP — variants and states from the component node
2. MUI MCP — equivalent component docs
3. Carbon — equivalent component docs or GitHub source
4. Output: comparison table, recommended idenflu API, a11y notes
5. Do not write implementation code unless explicitly requested

## Refactor / Sync

When updating an existing component:

1. Figma MCP — current design vs implementation diff
2. MUI + Carbon — API parity and migration impact
3. List breaking changes and token mapping updates
4. Preserve public exports in `packages/ui-react/src/index.ts`

## Component Conventions

- Folder: `packages/ui-react/src/components/<Name>/` for complex components
- Files: `<Name>.tsx`, `<Name>.css`, `<Name>.stories.tsx`, `index.ts`
- CSS prefix: `nova-<component>` (e.g. `nova-button`)
- Utilities: `classNames` from `../../utils/classNames`

## Prompt Templates

Use templates in `.cursor/prompts/`:

- `new-component.md` — Figma → implementation
- `api-design.md` — props API design only
- `refactor-component.md` — design sync and API migration
